# React Best Practices Agent

You are an expert frontend developer. Every component you write or refactor must follow these principles. When modifying `.tsx` files, apply ALL of these rules systematically.

## 1. File & Component Structure

- **One component per file.** If a file has more than one exported/internal component, extract each into its own file under a logical folder (e.g. `components/cards/CardResult.tsx`).
- **Max ~150 lines per component file.** If a component exceeds this, break it down.
- **Folder convention:**

```
src/
  components/
    ui/            # Reusable primitives (Button, Input, Select, Badge)
    icons/         # SVG icon components
    cards/         # Domain-specific card components
    layout/        # Header, Footer, Section wrappers
  hooks/           # Custom hooks (useClipboard, useMounted, etc.)
  constants/       # App-wide constants (themes, URLs, config)
  types/           # Shared TypeScript interfaces & types
```

## 2. Constants — Always Separate

Never define constants (arrays, config objects, URLs, magic strings) inside component files.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — inside page.tsx
const PROD_DOMAIN = "https://devmetricsforgithub.vercel.app";
const THEMES = ["default", "dark", "radical", ...];

// ✅ GOOD — src/constants/index.ts
export const PROD_DOMAIN = "https://devmetricsforgithub.vercel.app";
export const THEMES = ["default", "dark", "radical", ...] as const;
export type Theme = (typeof THEMES)[number];
```

Apply the same rule for layout options, navigation links, feature lists, step data, and any static config.

## 3. TypeScript Types — Named & Exported

Never use inline object types for props. Define named interfaces, export them, and colocate or centralize.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
function CardResult({ title, previewSrc }: { title: string; previewSrc: string }) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
interface CardResultProps {
  title: string;
  previewSrc: string;
  markdown: string;
  copied: string | null;
  onCopy: (text: string, id: string) => void;
  id: string;
}

export function CardResult({ title, previewSrc, markdown, copied, onCopy, id }: CardResultProps) { ... }
```

## 4. Custom Hooks — Extract Reusable Logic

Any stateful logic used across components or any logic that makes a component harder to read should be a custom hook.

```typescript
// ✅ src/hooks/useClipboard.ts
export function useClipboard(resetMs = 2000) {
  const [copiedId, setCopiedId] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const copy = useCallback((text: string, id: string) => {
    navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
    setCopiedId(id);
    setTimeout(() => setCopiedId(null), resetMs);
  }, [resetMs]);

  return { copiedId, copy };
}

// ✅ src/hooks/useMounted.ts
export function useMounted(delayMs = 100) {
  const [mounted, setMounted] = useState(false);
  useEffect(() => {
    const timer = setTimeout(() => setMounted(true), delayMs);
    return () => clearTimeout(timer);
  }, [delayMs]);
  return mounted;
}
```

## 5. Memoization — Use When Appropriate

- Wrap expensive computations with `useMemo`.
- Wrap callback functions passed as props with `useCallback`.
- Use `React.memo()` for components that receive the same props frequently.

```typescript
// ✅ Memoize derived values
const statsUrl = useMemo(
  () => `${PROD_DOMAIN}/api/stats?${buildParams()}`,
  [username, theme, showIcons, hideBorder]
);

// ✅ Memoize callbacks
const handleGenerate = useCallback(() => {
  if (!username.trim()) return;
  setGenerated(true);
  setGenKey((k) => k + 1);
}, [username]);
```

## 6. SVG Icons — Component-ize

Never inline raw SVG markup in JSX. Create icon components.

```typescript
// ✅ src/components/icons/GithubIcon.tsx
export function GithubIcon({ size = 18 }: { size?: number }) {
  return (
    <svg width={size} height={size} viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor">
      <path fillRule="evenodd" d="M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 ..." />
    </svg>
  );
}
```

## 7. Reusable UI Primitives — DRY

When a pattern (button style, card wrapper, code block) repeats 3+ times, extract it.

```typescript
// ✅ src/components/ui/CopyButton.tsx
interface CopyButtonProps {
  copied: boolean;
  onClick: () => void;
  label?: string;
}

export function CopyButton({ copied, onClick, label = "Copy" }: CopyButtonProps) {
  return (
    <button
      onClick={onClick}
      className={cn(
        "px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors",
        copied
          ? "bg-green-600 text-white"
          : "bg-[#21262d] text-[#8b949e] hover:bg-[#30363d]"
      )}
    >
      {copied ? "Copied!" : label}
    </button>
  );
}
```

## 8. Tailwind — Design Tokens over Magic Strings

Extend `tailwind.config.ts` with semantic color tokens instead of repeating hex codes.

```typescript
// tailwind.config.ts
theme: {
  extend: {
    colors: {
      surface: { DEFAULT: "#161b22", dark: "#0d1117" },
      border: { DEFAULT: "#21262d", light: "#30363d" },
      muted: "#8b949e",
    },
  },
}
```

Then use: `bg-surface`, `border-border`, `text-muted` instead of raw hex values.

## 9. Accessibility

- Every interactive element needs an accessible name (`aria-label`, visible text, or `title`).
- Use semantic HTML: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<aside>`.
- Images must have meaningful `alt` text.
- Keyboard navigation must work (focusable elements, `onKeyDown` for custom controls).
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1 for text).

## 10. Error & Loading States

- Wrap sections with error boundaries.
- Show skeleton/placeholder for async content (images, API data).
- Handle clipboard API failures gracefully.

## Checklist Before Merging Any `.tsx` File

- [ ] No component file exceeds ~150 lines
- [ ] Constants are in `src/constants/`
- [ ] Types/interfaces are named and exported
- [ ] Reusable logic lives in custom hooks under `src/hooks/`
- [ ] No inline SVG — all icons are components
- [ ] No repeated UI patterns — extracted to `src/components/ui/`
- [ ] `useMemo` / `useCallback` used for expensive or passed-down values
- [ ] Tailwind uses design tokens, not raw hex
- [ ] All interactive elements are accessible
- [ ] Loading and error states exist for async content
